<body>
    <h1>Task 20 - RAD</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 local-id=3D"794c2682373a" id=3D"Task20-RAD-1.Introduction">1. I=
ntroduction</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"7c791fff8f7a" id=3D"Task20-RAD-1.1Purpose">1.1 Purpose</h2>
<p local-id=3D"ec700723232e">The purpose of this document is to define the =
requirements for setting up a self-hosted DNS server and an AWS Route 53 ho=
sted zone, and to understand how DNS resolution changes when nameserver (NS=
) records are updated.</p>
<p local-id=3D"f84d232e19c8">This document is intended for:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d82226ec15d1">DevOps Engineers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3e65787f90a8">Cloud Engineers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"41574d691aa4">Students and Interns</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5d72a9c46b91">Project Evaluators</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"b71c29b6adf3" id=3D"Task20-RAD-1.2Scope">1.2 Scope</h2>
<p local-id=3D"deb2220e7313"><strong>Included in scope:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"038ff8b2fdd6">Setup of a self-hosted DNS server (BIND9 / Cor=
eDNS) on AWS EC2</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0dc19e115a11">Configuration of an AWS Route 53 public hosted=
 zone</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bc14e2a6b90c">Creation of DNS records (A record, CNAME recor=
d) in both DNS environments</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"52296c24baf1">NS record switching at the domain registrar to=
 change authoritative DNS</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1af15240fe8c">DNS resolution testing using command-line tool=
s (dig, nslookup)</p></li>
</ul>
<p local-id=3D"ff7a76ac6bad"><strong>Not included:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5db41a81d05e">Advanced DNS security (DNSSEC)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6f9f970687f2">High availability DNS clustering with primary =
and secondary nameservers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2c8a9aa410f3">Automation pipelines for DNS configuration man=
agement</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"dbf3495377ed" id=3D"Task20-RAD-1.3Definitions,Acronyms,andA=
bbreviations">1.3 Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"06d05840-e547-4bf2-a500-d01=
50f3b002e" class=3D"confluenceTable">
<tbody>
<tr>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"ceb1307aeb4d">Term</p></th>
<th class=3D"confluenceTh">
<p local-id=3D"2a1170c024f6">Meaning</p></th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"3653fa8fded4">DNS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"8fbf2c2bdd12">Domain Name System =E2=80=94 the system that t=
ranslates domain names to IP addresses</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"175dfbeefe00">NS</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"33e05d36990c">Name Server =E2=80=94 the server authoritative=
 for a DNS zone</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"19970c73a7c6">A Record</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"527f3bc5b473">DNS record that maps a domain name directly to=
 an IPv4 address</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"ae4fc4434505">CNAME</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"dadc5e442909">Canonical Name =E2=80=94 an alias record that =
points one domain to another</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"564b93a270ca">EC2</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"625f97dfe21e">Elastic Compute Cloud =E2=80=94 AWS virtual ma=
chine service</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"5144647f1fb3">Route 53</p></td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">
<p local-id=3D"cb4ef693a003">AWS managed DNS service with global Anycast in=
frastructure</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div>
<h2 local-id=3D"5f1bf77c722e" id=3D"Task20-RAD-1.4References">1.4 Reference=
s</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"74da7eb19738">AWS Route 53 Official Documentation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4c9ee3eab7c1">BIND9 Administrator Reference Manual</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"58a4e29e61cf">CoreDNS Documentation</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"acb477f2b3cd">DNS Concepts and Standards (RFC 1034, RFC 1035=
)</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"44f53d3c31bc" id=3D"Task20-RAD-1.5Overview">1.5 Overview</h=
2>
<p local-id=3D"bb2b0f07eb1c">This document includes:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"022c658cb458">DNS architecture overview for both the self-ho=
sted and Route 53 environments</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d02304d47ccb">Functional requirements and use cases covering=
 the full DNS setup and switchover workflow</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"15104ff97130">DNS testing procedures using dig and nslookup<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0c23399bfca8">Risk identification and mitigation strategies<=
/p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bdd0162ea2b1">Dependency analysis for the implementation</p>=
</li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"82547880008e" id=3D"Task20-RAD-2.ProjectOverview">2. Projec=
t Overview</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"699b919df3a6" id=3D"Task20-RAD-2.1ProjectObjectives">2.1 Pr=
oject Objectives</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"825c32b16e58">Deploy a self-hosted authoritative DNS server =
(BIND9) on an AWS EC2 instance</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3d4adc67266e">Configure a public hosted zone in AWS Route 53=
 for the same domain</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"66ca5a734722">Create equivalent DNS records (A record, CNAME=
 record) in both DNS environments</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f927d35085e4">Switch NS records at the domain registrar and =
observe the change in DNS authority</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"31a5f3c3ffc5">Test and validate DNS resolution using dig and=
 nslookup before and after the NS switch</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"c89326faa115" id=3D"Task20-RAD-2.2BusinessGoals">2.2 Busine=
ss Goals</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"151f84d63df7">Develop a practical understanding of how DNS r=
esolution works end-to-end</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ca0dd956d6a5">Compare the operational characteristics of sel=
f-hosted DNS versus managed DNS (Route 53)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e3380befebea">Understand how NS records define DNS authority=
 and how changing them transfers control</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"775a062b4419">Build hands-on experience with DNS configurati=
on, zone files, and diagnostic tools</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"4366677f88bc" id=3D"Task20-RAD-2.3Background">2.3 Backgroun=
d</h2>
<p local-id=3D"1aca7536ee1b">ABC Technologies wants to evaluate and compare=
 two approaches to DNS management for its internal domains:</p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2b7e266c75ee">A self-hosted DNS server running on AWS EC2</p=
></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"eb828c63acb6">A fully managed DNS service using AWS Route 53=
</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"0572d47f3090">Traditionally, DNS is delegated to domain regi=
strars or third-party DNS providers. This project gives the engineering tea=
m direct, hands-on experience with DNS internals =E2=80=94 specifically how=
 NS records define which server is authoritative for a domain, how switchin=
g NS records transfers DNS authority between providers, and how DNS propaga=
tion behavior differs between the two approaches. The outcome will inform A=
BC Technologies' DNS strategy for future internal and production domain man=
agement.</p>
<h2 local-id=3D"482217d458bf" id=3D"Task20-RAD-2.4Constraints">2.4 Constrai=
nts</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cbd03d995da6">DNS propagation delays after NS record changes=
 can range from seconds to 48 hours depending on TTL values and upstream ca=
ching</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b96a6604793e">A static public IP address is required on the =
EC2 instance for it to function as a reachable external nameserver</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1ca2860bcaf4">NS record changes depend on access to and coop=
eration of the domain registrar</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0c52b90d697c">Manual configuration of BIND9 zone files requi=
res careful syntax management =E2=80=94 errors prevent the DNS service from=
 starting</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"28b9168cf503" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.FunctionalRequirements">3.=
 Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"eae44a01b0d0" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.1UseCaseDiagram">3.1 Use C=
ase Diagram</h2><span class=3D"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-cente=
r-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size"><img class=3D"confluence-embedde=
d-image image-center" alt=3D"image-20260322-122321.png" width=3D"468" loadi=
ng=3D"lazy" src=3D"142cf06b1659e8abc15f285ae684658ae2b10434871fc17c0b20daaf=
20ae5d3a" data-image-src=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki/download/atta=
chments/1885602357/image-20260322-122321.png?version=3D1&amp;modificationDa=
te=3D1774182209574&amp;cacheVersion=3D1&amp;api=3Dv2" data-height=3D"2484" =
data-width=3D"4764" data-unresolved-comment-count=3D"0" data-linked-resourc=
e-id=3D"1886912955" data-linked-resource-version=3D"1" data-linked-resource=
-type=3D"attachment" data-linked-resource-default-alias=3D"image-20260322-1=
22321.png" data-base-url=3D"https://iamops.atlassian.net/wiki" data-linked-=
resource-content-type=3D"image/png" data-linked-resource-container-id=3D"18=
85602357" data-linked-resource-container-version=3D"2" data-media-id=3D"4ce=
f970e-6336-4ac1-9da6-c93894f2821b" data-media-type=3D"file" height=3D"244">=
</span>
<h2 local-id=3D"0296d35c90e0" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2UseCases">3.2 Use Cases</=
h2>
<h3 local-id=3D"ab6a8da72670" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2.1UseCase1:SetupSelf-Host=
edDNSServer(BIND9/CoreDNS)">3.2.1 Use Case 1: Setup Self-Hosted DNS Server =
(BIND9 / CoreDNS)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"12a3d765d815"><strong>Description:</strong> Deploy and confi=
gure an authoritative DNS server on an AWS EC2 instance to serve DNS record=
s for the target domain zone.</p>
<p local-id=3D"750a5bd89c95"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Engineer</p>
<p local-id=3D"f424d5babea8"><strong>Preconditions:</strong> EC2 instance i=
s running and accessible via SSH; public IP is assigned</p>
<p local-id=3D"9f687047b142"><strong>Postconditions:</strong> DNS server is=
 active and responds correctly to external DNS queries on port 53</p>
<p local-id=3D"379a0e0ffe34"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4fe81d5641d9">Launch EC2 instance with Ubuntu and assign a p=
ublic IP</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cb0152f8b480">Install BIND9 or CoreDNS via the package manag=
er</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"432a84d26ce3">Configure the named.conf.local zone declaratio=
n</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3d08a1d66b70">Create and populate the zone data file with SO=
A, NS, and A records</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3a2d02588acf">Open port 53 (UDP and TCP) in the EC2 Security=
 Group</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"610790690e87">Start and enable the DNS service via systemd</=
p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"72aba8015d0e"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong> Zone file =
misconfiguration =E2=86=92 BIND9 fails to start; validate with named-checkz=
one before restarting</p>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"4667fb38b7fa" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2.2UseCase2:CreateDNSRecor=
ds(A,CNAME)">3.2.2 Use Case 2: Create DNS Records (A, CNAME)</h3>
<p local-id=3D"db4753a28ba6"><strong>Description:</strong> Create DNS resou=
rce records in both the self-hosted BIND9 zone file and the Route 53 hosted=
 zone to enable domain name resolution.</p>
<p local-id=3D"a368b8787b0f"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Engineer</p>
<p local-id=3D"55eea488d535"><strong>Preconditions:</strong> DNS server or =
hosted zone is active and ready to accept record configuration</p>
<p local-id=3D"87fd53cb8e26"><strong>Postconditions:</strong> DNS records r=
esolve correctly when queried</p>
<p local-id=3D"1ee2dec9fb69"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f28f2b1d545f">Create an A record mapping the domain to the E=
C2 public IP</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2f9c05f0cc7f">Create a CNAME record as an alias pointing to =
the primary domain</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"233648c1f120">Save the zone file and increment the SOA seria=
l number</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3243317eca30">Reload the DNS service to apply the new record=
s</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a5fbadb99dc8">Validate with dig @localhost</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"034c2b34dc96"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong> Incorrect =
record syntax =E2=86=92 resolution returns NXDOMAIN or wrong IP; re-check z=
one file and reload</p>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"2e39d9a1aac3" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2.3UseCase3:SetupRoute53Ho=
stedZone">3.2.3 Use Case 3: Setup Route 53 Hosted Zone</h3>
<p local-id=3D"81094ae1fbe8"><strong>Description:</strong> Create and confi=
gure a public hosted zone in AWS Route 53 for the target domain with equiva=
lent DNS records.</p>
<p local-id=3D"75c457eff5aa"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Engineer</p>
<p local-id=3D"7797c83d947b"><strong>Preconditions:</strong> AWS account is=
 accessible with Route 53 permissions; domain is registered</p>
<p local-id=3D"cae09c55ea6c"><strong>Postconditions:</strong> Hosted zone i=
s active and DNS records are visible via Route 53 nameservers</p>
<p local-id=3D"7a768e2da9b8"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"34a9a1889024">Navigate to Route 53 and create a public hoste=
d zone for the domain</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"05b2b474bf8d">Add DNS records (A record, CNAME record) match=
ing those in the BIND9 zone</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"29acb394e550">Verify record configuration in the hosted zone=
 console</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"97e7abd76a6e">Note the four Route 53 NS record values assign=
ed to the hosted zone</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"843f88f92da8"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong> Missing or=
 incorrect records =E2=86=92 DNS queries return no answer; add missing reco=
rds and re-test</p>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"462bca06b3e8" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2.4UseCase4:ConfigureNSRec=
ordsatRegistrar">3.2.4 Use Case 4: Configure NS Records at Registrar</h3>
<p local-id=3D"8374ecec8b85"><strong>Description:</strong> Update the domai=
n's nameserver records at the domain registrar to point DNS authority to th=
e chosen DNS provider.</p>
<p local-id=3D"86036f76d136"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Engineer, Doma=
in Registrar</p>
<p local-id=3D"a96ce5effa0d"><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Domain is regi=
stered; target DNS server (BIND9 or Route 53) is fully configured and respo=
nding</p>
<p local-id=3D"3b55dc61308c"><strong>Postconditions:</strong> DNS authority=
 is updated and queries are routed to the new nameserver</p>
<p local-id=3D"edd18549b2d4"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fb8bd81a9835">Log in to the domain registrar's management co=
nsole</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ef6dba63f076">Navigate to the domain's DNS / nameserver sett=
ings</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7d2e9df5e8e1">Replace the current NS values with the new nam=
eserver addresses (EC2 IP or Route 53 NS records)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5c6f5b8dff53">Save the changes</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b0c61139fc0a">Wait for propagation to complete (TTL-dependen=
t)</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"c8056c0bdf51"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong> Incorrect =
NS values entered =E2=86=92 domain stops resolving; correct the NS records =
immediately and monitor propagation</p>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"1c70d005defc" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2.5UseCase5:SwitchBetweenD=
NSProviders">3.2.5 Use Case 5: Switch Between DNS Providers</h3>
<p local-id=3D"770b8ee744f8"><strong>Description:</strong> Switch DNS autho=
rity between the self-hosted EC2 BIND9 server and AWS Route 53 by updating =
NS records, and observe the change in resolution behavior.</p>
<p local-id=3D"e95b7a2e3ad1"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Engineer</p>
<p local-id=3D"868b8d762041"><strong>Preconditions:</strong> Both DNS envir=
onments (BIND9 and Route 53) are fully configured with equivalent records</=
p>
<p local-id=3D"a6ccbd23a93a"><strong>Postconditions:</strong> DNS resolutio=
n reflects the active nameserver after propagation completes</p>
<p local-id=3D"baeeca0541e3"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"be82f5f8b42c">Point domain NS records to the EC2 BIND9 serve=
r</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"3d3b03bb35e4">Test DNS resolution using dig =E2=80=94 confir=
m BIND9 is the authoritative server</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"2aed54b4b9a5">Update NS records to point to Route 53 nameser=
vers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"dab43ee26ea2">Test DNS resolution again =E2=80=94 confirm Ro=
ute 53 is now authoritative</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"94949ab3a9d1">Compare resolution behavior, TTL, and response=
 source between both states</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"c76c82b06c54"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong> Propagatio=
n delay causes cached results to persist =E2=80=94 wait for TTL expiry and =
re-test; use dig +trace to monitor live propagation</p>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"839b94cbaa6c" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2.6UseCase6:TestDNSResolut=
ion(dig/nslookup)">3.2.6 Use Case 6: Test DNS Resolution (dig / nslookup)</=
h3>
<p local-id=3D"a32113ff3833"><strong>Description:</strong> Use DNS diagnost=
ic tools to verify that queries return correct responses and to identify wh=
ich DNS server is answering.</p>
<p local-id=3D"fbe930cc0ee1"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Engineer, End =
User / DNS Client</p>
<p local-id=3D"1611c437d4cd"><strong>Preconditions:</strong> DNS records ar=
e configured and the DNS server is reachable</p>
<p local-id=3D"ae4fa4a8a558"><strong>Postconditions:</strong> DNS responses=
 are validated and the authoritative server is confirmed</p>
<p local-id=3D"1e2c6386a3bc"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"bbaaf5f60ab6">Run dig @&lt;server-ip&gt; &lt;domain&gt; to q=
uery a specific nameserver directly</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"b7f910fbe117">Run dig +trace &lt;domain&gt; to trace the ful=
l resolution path from root servers</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"7f32a825605c">Run nslookup &lt;domain&gt; for a quick intera=
ctive verification</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"051cd0fb501f">Review the ANSWER SECTION for the returned IP =
or CNAME value</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a261d8ee89c2">Check the SERVER field to confirm which DNS se=
rver answered the query</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"e8cd8776a383"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong> No respons=
e received =E2=86=92 check port 53 Security Group rules, BIND9 service stat=
us, and EC2 reachability</p>
<hr>
<h3 local-id=3D"61c9839ec4aa" id=3D"Task20-RAD-3.2.7UseCase7:ValidateDNSPro=
pagationandResponses">3.2.7 Use Case 7: Validate DNS Propagation and Respon=
ses</h3>
<p local-id=3D"7a98dfeb4755"><strong>Description:</strong> Observe and conf=
irm DNS changes after an NS record update by querying from multiple resolve=
rs and tracking when the new authoritative server begins responding.</p>
<p local-id=3D"0433f1023a98"><strong>Actors:</strong> DevOps Engineer</p>
<p local-id=3D"ec37b5e1bd0f"><strong>Preconditions:</strong> NS records hav=
e been updated at the registrar</p>
<p local-id=3D"742594b998b8"><strong>Postconditions:</strong> DNS propagati=
on is confirmed and the new authoritative server is responding globally</p>
<p local-id=3D"4974ba5ad748"><strong>Flow of Events:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e99b7c4c60f1">Query the domain repeatedly using dig +trace i=
mmediately after the NS change</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"cd2d6d230593">Compare response sources =E2=80=94 old server =
vs new server =E2=80=94 to observe the propagation transition</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a3fa2bb4a601">Identify the authoritative server in the final=
 hop of the dig +trace output</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8395e8602780">Confirm propagation is complete when all queri=
es return the new authoritative server's response</p></li>
</ol>
<p local-id=3D"4e0203e1a60c"><strong>Alternative Flows:</strong> Cached res=
ults from the previous nameserver persist =E2=80=94 this is expected behavi=
or; wait for the previous NS record TTL to expire before re-testing</p>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"a04ad32d6840" id=3D"Task20-RAD-4.Non-FunctionalRequirements=
">4. Non-Functional Requirements</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"c3709dee220e" id=3D"Task20-RAD-4.1PerformanceRequirements">=
4.1 Performance Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"c2a36a1a8ec2">DNS query responses should return within accep=
table latency (typically under 100ms for cached responses)</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"db3627bd79ac">The BIND9 server should handle concurrent DNS =
queries without degradation on a t2.micro / t3.micro EC2 instance</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"f94386a4f5c9">Route 53 leverages AWS Anycast infrastructure =
=E2=80=94 sub-millisecond global resolution latency</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"f5df0319fc50" id=3D"Task20-RAD-4.2SecurityRequirements">4.2=
 Security Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"fb796d245042">EC2 Security Group must restrict inbound port =
53 (UDP/TCP) to required sources only =E2=80=94 not open to 0.0.0.0/0 in pr=
oduction</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"1727e0e653ac">BIND9 must be configured as authoritative-only=
 (recursion no;) to prevent use as an open resolver for DNS amplification a=
ttacks</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0a90ac0f7758">Zone transfer must be restricted (allow-transf=
er { none; };) to prevent unauthorized zone data exfiltration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"5a96a41d443c">SSH access (port 22) to the EC2 instance must =
be restricted to the administrator's IP</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"e7239d0b3460" id=3D"Task20-RAD-4.3UsabilityRequirements">4.=
3 Usability Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"791987a65694">DNS records must be clearly documented with re=
cord type, name, value, and TTL for easy management and handover</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"6ae213017174">BIND9 zone file changes must be validated usin=
g named-checkzone before every service reload</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"e519e1c672ba">Testing commands (dig, nslookup) must be docum=
ented with expected output for each validation step</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"8d5f8e2dffee" id=3D"Task20-RAD-4.4ReliabilityRequirements">=
4.4 Reliability Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"a38bc7949346">The BIND9 DNS service must be configured to st=
art automatically on EC2 instance reboot via systemd enable</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"ca3d7fe9adf4">Route 53 provides 100% uptime SLA =E2=80=94 us=
ed as the reliable fallback if the self-hosted server becomes unavailable</=
p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0155d108b9fc">DNS records must be consistent between both en=
vironments to ensure resolution works regardless of which nameserver is act=
ive</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"1b9aaee0f029" id=3D"Task20-RAD-4.5ComplianceRequirements">4=
.5 Compliance Requirements</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"d2e6314be331">DNS zone configuration must follow RFC 1034 an=
d RFC 1035 standards for zone file format and record types</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"4e693a628814">SOA serial numbers must be incremented on ever=
y zone file change to ensure caching resolvers detect updates</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"23a95d1b3fe5">Domain NS records must be managed responsibly =
=E2=80=94 changes should only be made by authorized personnel with document=
ed approval</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h1 local-id=3D"dba09afaf8e2" id=3D"Task20-RAD-5.AssumptionsandDependencies=
">5. Assumptions and Dependencies</h1>
<h2 local-id=3D"000c8c9c8354" id=3D"Task20-RAD-5.1Assumptions">5.1 Assumpti=
ons</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"736acecc3229">A domain name is available and registered with=
 a registrar that allows custom NS record configuration</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"33dc3428bf88">AWS services (EC2, Route 53) are accessible wi=
th appropriate IAM permissions</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"8ba0252943dc">The EC2 instance running BIND9 has a static pu=
blic IP address that does not change between reboots</p></li>
<li>
<p local-id=3D"0b860f8923bb">The engineer has shell access to the EC2 insta=
nce via SSH for BIND9 configuration and testing</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 local-id=3D"06da9c9b2e17" id=3D"Task20-RAD-5.2Dependencies">5.2 Depende=
ncies</h2>
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table data-layout=3D"default" data-local-id=3D"b0371dc5-1a60-4332-a060-a43=
3f18c8d22" class=3D"confluenceTable">
